00:05:49.920 --> 00:05:54.280
OK, so we are also going to
talk about two important things.

00:05:55.390 --> 00:05:59.790
Please don't forget that when we
are talking about accessibility

00:05:59.790 --> 00:06:05.910
or digital accessibility, we cannot
dismiss the specific language

00:06:05.910 --> 00:06:09.610
that is required to
create our content, OK?

00:06:09.610 --> 00:06:13.460
So that's why it's important
to understand about disability.

00:06:13.460 --> 00:06:18.400
Disability is something
that everyone has.

00:06:18.400 --> 00:06:19.570
Everyone.

00:06:19.570 --> 00:06:23.420
It's not something that you need
to weigh when you get older.

00:06:23.420 --> 00:06:25.910
No, it's something that
is always in our life.

00:06:25.910 --> 00:06:29.540
This is something that is normal,
but actually is not something

00:06:29.540 --> 00:06:33.660
that we talk about much,
and it's important to discuss.

00:06:33.660 --> 00:06:34.660
There are two important points.

00:06:35.650 --> 00:06:39.760
First point is that there are
common internet disabilities.

00:06:39.760 --> 00:06:45.200
So for example, vision, cognitive
disabilities, hearing impairments,

00:06:45.200 --> 00:06:47.040
reduces mobility.

00:06:47.040 --> 00:06:52.300
Those are the most common disability
that we can find statistically

00:06:52.300 --> 00:06:55.580
on the internet that
we need to think about,

00:06:55.580 --> 00:06:58.230
even when we start
planning our projects.

00:06:58.230 --> 00:07:00.640
It's not when we are
on the testing part.

00:07:00.640 --> 00:07:05.240
It's when we start to creating
the ideas or generating the ideas

00:07:05.240 --> 00:07:06.820
to create our project.

00:07:06.820 --> 00:07:09.880
Next, of course, is the
dimensions of these disabilities.

00:07:09.880 --> 00:07:15.470
Some of them could be an impairment,
which is specifically related

00:07:15.470 --> 00:07:18.270
to a composition of
the body of a person,

00:07:18.270 --> 00:07:23.210
or if a person is not able
to memorize the information

00:07:23.210 --> 00:07:30.240
in the fastest ways possible
or they will be lost.

00:07:30.240 --> 00:07:33.760
And, of course, some types of
restrictions of participation;

00:07:33.760 --> 00:07:35.110
for example, physical space.

00:07:36.310 --> 00:07:39.250
So why should we always try
to do this at the beginning

00:07:39.250 --> 00:07:40.340
of our conversations?

00:07:40.340 --> 00:07:43.710
It’s because we cannot forget
that when we are talking

00:07:43.710 --> 00:07:47.210
about accessibility,
we are talking about people.

00:07:47.210 --> 00:07:51.350
We are not talking only about
the patches that I’m adding

00:07:51.350 --> 00:07:55.810
in the code with an Aria
attribute or with a label,

00:07:55.810 --> 00:07:56.970
and that would be enough.

00:07:56.970 --> 00:07:59.110
No, we are talking
about something else.

00:07:59.110 --> 00:08:03.050
Accessibility is a way
of living for many users,

00:08:03.050 --> 00:08:06.130
so that's why it's important
for us to understand that, OK?

00:08:06.130 --> 00:08:09.990
So based on that, I would like
to refer to two concepts that,

00:08:09.990 --> 00:08:13.480
for me, are really important in
order to review the best practices

00:08:13.480 --> 00:08:17.280
that we want to share today
about the visualizations.

00:08:17.280 --> 00:08:19.730
One of these is the
concept of usability.

00:08:19.730 --> 00:08:22.970
When we are talking about
usability and accessibility,

00:08:22.970 --> 00:08:25.970
we think that they are
separate, right?

00:08:25.970 --> 00:08:30.670
And one is one thing and
the other is another thing,

00:08:30.670 --> 00:08:33.410
but actually it’s not; it's
completely the opposite.

00:08:35.830 --> 00:08:40.700
[Inaudible 00:08:34],
we are talking about effectiveness.

00:08:40.700 --> 00:08:44.530
We are talking about how the
product is created in the way

00:08:44.530 --> 00:08:49.530
that is meeting with the needs that
I have as a user in this specific

00:08:49.530 --> 00:08:51.120
or particular product.

00:08:51.120 --> 00:08:54.176
And when we're talking
about accessibility,

00:08:54.177 --> 00:08:56.120
we are talking specifically

00:08:56.120 --> 00:09:03.310
in the way, How can I definitely
test if my page is really usable

00:09:03.310 --> 00:09:08.860
when we are not using the
common patterns of navigation

00:09:08.860 --> 00:09:10.138
or interaction?

00:09:10.139 --> 00:09:13.970
For example, navigating the
page using a screen reader,

00:09:13.970 --> 00:09:18.710
or navigating the page
using a keyboard alone,

00:09:18.710 --> 00:09:23.420
or using magnification
tools, or a braille display.

00:09:23.420 --> 00:09:29.740
So how usable is my site when
I need to use external devices

00:09:29.740 --> 00:09:31.530
or assistive technologies?

00:09:31.530 --> 00:09:34.900
Is it still usable in the
way that I think it's usable?

00:09:34.900 --> 00:09:38.033
So that's why it's important.

00:09:38.033 --> 00:09:38.760
[Inaudible 00:09:38]

00:09:38.760 --> 00:09:40.230
prepare for you.

00:09:40.230 --> 00:09:43.780
Talking about usability,
this is the ability of the user

00:09:43.780 --> 00:09:48.880
to navigate the page, understand
the page, recover from errors,

00:09:48.880 --> 00:09:52.257
understand the content,
and also understand

00:09:52.258 --> 00:09:54.560
that everything is intuitive,

00:09:54.560 --> 00:09:55.720
OK?

00:09:55.720 --> 00:09:58.400
When we are talking
about accessibility,

00:09:58.400 --> 00:10:02.390
we are talking about keyboard
navigation, screen-reader users,

00:10:02.390 --> 00:10:06.440
magnification tools, and all the
tools that would be necessary

00:10:06.440 --> 00:10:09.270
for people with disabilities
to access the content.

00:10:11.110 --> 00:10:16.630
OK, so everything that I’ve
said is really important.

00:10:16.630 --> 00:10:19.380
It's like a small
summary about that.

00:10:19.380 --> 00:10:23.070
So [Inaudible 00:10:20],
so I don't need any more.

00:10:23.070 --> 00:10:27.471
In this case,
what is data visualization meant

00:10:27.472 --> 00:10:30.000
to do in our conversation?

00:10:30.000 --> 00:10:33.546
When we think about
data visualization,

00:10:33.547 --> 00:10:35.940
one of the first questions

00:10:35.940 --> 00:10:41.580
that I usually try to just
moderate when we want to work

00:10:41.580 --> 00:10:47.110
with designers or we developers
is [Inaudible 00:10:46]

00:10:47.110 --> 00:10:49.590
our users are going
to do with this?

00:10:49.590 --> 00:10:53.320
What would be the type of
decisions they need to take

00:10:53.320 --> 00:10:55.850
when we are creating
visualizations?

00:10:55.850 --> 00:11:01.390
Sometimes we think that we can create
the most beautiful visualization,

00:11:01.390 --> 00:11:04.730
but in general,
it's not useful enough.

00:11:04.730 --> 00:11:11.030
Or the lack of concepts that
are clear, it's really difficult

00:11:11.030 --> 00:11:12.450
to understand.

00:11:12.450 --> 00:11:17.110
And of course, how are we
going to make this accessible?

00:11:17.110 --> 00:11:24.780
Sometimes we think, OK, Merary,
but how much is the percentage

00:11:24.780 --> 00:11:28.950
of people with disabilities
that will use our system?

00:11:28.950 --> 00:11:31.960
And I was, like, Oh, my
God, this is not a question

00:11:31.960 --> 00:11:36.170
that I really like to answer,
and I will not answer anyways.

00:11:36.170 --> 00:11:39.760
But we need to think,
when we are creating content,

00:11:39.760 --> 00:11:42.610
that this content
needs to be accessible

00:11:42.610 --> 00:11:45.640
even if only one person
will access the product

00:11:45.640 --> 00:11:50.240
or 1000 user will use our product.

00:11:50.240 --> 00:11:52.300
So we always need
to think about that.

00:11:52.300 --> 00:11:56.930
But always think about, What is
the purpose of the visualization?

00:11:56.930 --> 00:12:00.760
Is it possible to create an
accessible visualization?

00:12:00.760 --> 00:12:05.200
This is the second most important
question that you need to ask.

00:12:05.200 --> 00:12:11.550
OK, so what are the most common
barriers that we can find

00:12:11.550 --> 00:12:16.820
or we can face when we are
navigating or creating visualizations

00:12:16.820 --> 00:12:18.220
in terms of accessibility?

00:12:19.510 --> 00:12:22.940
Sometimes we say OK,
we're talking about visualizations;

00:12:22.940 --> 00:12:26.840
of course we need to
prioritize the visual part.

00:12:26.840 --> 00:12:33.970
But sometimes we prioritize
that so much that the navigation

00:12:33.970 --> 00:12:38.640
or understandability of the
graphic, it's impossible.

00:12:38.640 --> 00:12:43.870
So visually, it's beautiful,
it's presentable, but it's difficult

00:12:43.870 --> 00:12:47.770
to understand, it's difficult
to use and make decisions,

00:12:47.770 --> 00:12:50.340
and, of course,
it’s difficult to navigate.

00:12:50.340 --> 00:12:54.960
And sometimes it's lacking of a lot
of context, so it's not possible

00:12:54.960 --> 00:12:56.580
to understand.

00:12:56.580 --> 00:12:59.700
On the other side,
we have the color schemes.

00:12:59.700 --> 00:13:00.520
What is that?

00:13:00.520 --> 00:13:05.890
Sometimes we have beautiful colors,
and we have all the rainbow there,

00:13:05.890 --> 00:13:06.710
right?

00:13:06.710 --> 00:13:11.680
And we create a graphic not
in a specific set of colors.

00:13:11.680 --> 00:13:16.470
So we can add all the color that I
have available without restriction.

00:13:16.470 --> 00:13:20.320
There is not a pattern or
there is not a specific set

00:13:20.320 --> 00:13:26.100
or matrix using colors, so the user
is able to customize everything

00:13:26.100 --> 00:13:27.300
as they want.

00:13:27.300 --> 00:13:30.000
One of the things that I would
like to mention with this is that,

00:13:30.000 --> 00:13:34.260
in one of the previous companies
that I had, they gave the power

00:13:34.260 --> 00:13:37.690
to the users to
customize everything.

00:13:37.690 --> 00:13:41.460
So one of the biggest
challenges they had is that,

00:13:42.520 --> 00:13:46.630
How can we just restrict a
little bit more the customization

00:13:46.630 --> 00:13:50.490
in the way that when they
are creating the content,

00:13:50.490 --> 00:13:54.560
they also create
accessible customizations?

00:13:54.560 --> 00:13:58.240
So that's why it's necessary to
create a specific set of tools

00:13:58.240 --> 00:14:00.960
that we are going to
share today with you.

00:14:00.960 --> 00:14:03.120
Another thing, of course,
is the navigation.

00:14:03.120 --> 00:14:07.400
So we need to think about
multiple ways of interaction

00:14:07.400 --> 00:14:09.970
when we are navigating
with our visualizations.

00:14:09.970 --> 00:14:12.440
We need to think about
keyword navigation.

00:14:12.440 --> 00:14:17.600
It's not the same to navigate
our page using a laptop

00:14:17.600 --> 00:14:23.640
or desktop keyboard,
or using the mouse with a keyword,

00:14:23.640 --> 00:14:28.060
or just using the keyword
itself and just the mouse pad

00:14:28.060 --> 00:14:29.680
from our laptop.

00:14:29.680 --> 00:14:32.930
All the interactions are
different, and that's why we need

00:14:32.930 --> 00:14:36.970
to understand what will also
be the way that the users needs

00:14:36.970 --> 00:14:39.400
to interact with our page.

00:14:39.400 --> 00:14:40.710
So those are the most common.

00:14:40.710 --> 00:14:45.830
So it's the use of colors and also
the way that the users navigate

00:14:45.830 --> 00:14:47.420
or interacts with the pages.

00:14:47.420 --> 00:14:51.619
And of course,
when the prioritization

00:14:51.620 --> 00:14:54.310
of the visual components

00:14:54.310 --> 00:14:55.520
or [Inaudible 00:14:54]

00:14:59.530 --> 00:15:02.170
the presentation is the
priority, [Inaudible 00:15:01]

00:15:02.170 --> 00:15:03.170
clear context.

00:15:03.930 --> 00:15:10.320
So what are the best practices
that we can just find for today

00:15:10.320 --> 00:15:12.450
and we can share with you?

00:15:12.450 --> 00:15:16.490
One of the best practices that
I can share with you today is

00:15:16.490 --> 00:15:20.230
that you need to humanize the data.

00:15:20.230 --> 00:15:23.070
What is the meaning of that?

00:15:23.070 --> 00:15:27.820
Think about what will be
the value that we can find

00:15:27.820 --> 00:15:31.320
or we can obtain from
this visualization.

00:15:34.290 --> 00:15:38.760
That I need to make in order
to use the information.

00:15:38.760 --> 00:15:45.050
What will be the specific situation
that I need to review with this?

00:15:45.050 --> 00:15:50.010
So always try to create
the data in a way

00:15:50.010 --> 00:15:53.820
that the user will be
able to understand.

00:15:53.820 --> 00:15:59.860
Also, try to create the content in
a way that will be intuitive, right?

00:15:59.860 --> 00:16:01.500
Intuitive for the users.

00:16:01.500 --> 00:16:02.500
Why is this important?

00:16:02.500 --> 00:16:07.240
Because when we need to make
decisions, there are times of the day

00:16:07.240 --> 00:16:11.100
that we can just make a decision,
and sometimes there is not.

00:16:11.100 --> 00:16:15.630
For example, if we have multiple
meetings during the morning

00:16:15.630 --> 00:16:18.430
and during the afternoon,
I need to make a decision

00:16:18.430 --> 00:16:23.550
and I need to go to a specific
visualization, and I'm exhausted

00:16:23.550 --> 00:16:25.820
because I had a lot of meetings.

00:16:25.820 --> 00:16:31.030
There’s a cognitive load there
that probably can not help me

00:16:31.030 --> 00:16:34.669
to create great data or
make decisions correctly

00:16:34.670 --> 00:16:36.080
because I'm tired.

00:16:36.080 --> 00:16:39.240
This is something that is
also necessary to think about.

00:16:39.240 --> 00:16:43.690
Mental health, invisible disabilities
is something that is important

00:16:43.690 --> 00:16:45.450
when we are talking about data.

00:16:45.450 --> 00:16:48.130
So first step, humanize the data.

00:16:49.650 --> 00:16:54.040
The second point is
assistive-technology interaction.

00:16:54.040 --> 00:16:56.090
What is the meaning of that?

00:16:56.090 --> 00:17:00.330
So we need to be completely
conscious about the use

00:17:00.330 --> 00:17:02.290
of assistive technology.

00:17:02.290 --> 00:17:06.308
If you want to start
working with accessibility

00:17:06.309 --> 00:17:08.400
and you are a developer,

00:17:08.400 --> 00:17:14.180
or tester, designer,
project manager who definitely wants

00:17:14.180 --> 00:17:18.660
to start working with accessibility,
I really recommend you

00:17:18.660 --> 00:17:24.980
to start learning about
how to use a screen reader.

00:17:24.980 --> 00:17:26.090
Why is this important?

00:17:26.090 --> 00:17:29.310
Because every screen
reader is different

00:17:29.310 --> 00:17:34.370
and every browser versus the
screen reader is also different.

00:17:34.370 --> 00:17:38.040
The shortcuts are different
to access all the information

00:17:38.040 --> 00:17:39.180
from the screen readers.

00:17:40.790 --> 00:17:44.340
So that's why it's necessary for
you to understand the variations.

00:17:44.340 --> 00:17:46.010
Let me give you an example.

00:17:46.010 --> 00:17:52.880
If you want to use Edge as part of
the support browser from your system,

00:17:52.880 --> 00:17:56.810
you need to understand that the
best screen reader will be JAWS.

00:17:57.990 --> 00:18:02.350
In the case of Chrome,
the best screen reader will be NVDA,

00:18:02.350 --> 00:18:04.130
and those are for Windows.

00:18:04.130 --> 00:18:08.983
But what is going on if you need
to test your product in Safari,

00:18:08.984 --> 00:18:10.600
on a Mac?

00:18:10.600 --> 00:18:12.040
What will be the screen reader?

00:18:12.040 --> 00:18:14.150
That will be Voiceover.

00:18:14.150 --> 00:18:17.200
Although, in this case, we are
talking about desktop environments.

00:18:17.200 --> 00:18:20.820
But what is going on if we
need to test our devices?

00:18:20.820 --> 00:18:25.720
So if we want to test our
products in Android, we need

00:18:25.720 --> 00:18:29.530
to get familiar with TalkBack,
which is the screen reader

00:18:29.530 --> 00:18:32.400
that is by default on
the operating system.

00:18:32.400 --> 00:18:36.700
Same case with Apple
devices, Voiceover.

00:18:36.700 --> 00:18:42.240
So it's really necessary to
understand why this is important.

00:18:42.240 --> 00:18:43.890
Why am I saying that?

00:18:43.890 --> 00:18:49.180
Because you will have multiple
components and interactions.

00:18:49.180 --> 00:18:52.070
For example,
if you are creating a website

00:18:52.070 --> 00:18:59.100
and you are using HTML5
components, usually,

00:18:59.100 --> 00:19:05.970
the screen readers are able to
identify those controls or components

00:19:05.970 --> 00:19:06.870
without any problem.

00:19:06.870 --> 00:19:09.870
That's why we are calling this
part accessibility supportive.

00:19:10.880 --> 00:19:18.880
Usually, all the native HTML5
controls are, 90% of the time,

00:19:20.090 --> 00:19:23.980
accessible by the
screen reader alone.

00:19:23.980 --> 00:19:27.630
But what happens when you
customize a component,

00:19:27.630 --> 00:19:31.790
and this component is not
including all the attributes

00:19:31.790 --> 00:19:36.230
to allow the screen reader
to understand your content?

00:19:36.230 --> 00:19:39.980
That's why it's necessary
to always keep in mind

00:19:39.980 --> 00:19:43.720
what will be the best way
to create our elements,

00:19:43.720 --> 00:19:46.810
or when we are creating
our visualizations.

00:19:46.810 --> 00:19:51.230
What will be the type of
components that we want to create?

00:19:51.230 --> 00:19:54.510
Is the user familiar
with those controls?

00:19:54.510 --> 00:19:58.480
For example, drop-down menus,
radio groups, checkboxes;

00:19:58.480 --> 00:20:01.410
all of those are really
familiar for users.

00:20:01.410 --> 00:20:04.810
But what is going on if you
need to create a specific

00:20:04.810 --> 00:20:06.580
and different interaction

00:20:06.581 --> 00:20:10.120
that probably the user
needs to take 10 seconds,

00:20:10.120 --> 00:20:14.480
one minute to think
about in order to use it?

00:20:15.700 --> 00:20:18.400
Another point that I would
like to mention is, the way

00:20:18.400 --> 00:20:22.181
that this element
needs to be created,

00:20:22.182 --> 00:20:25.090
you need to think about that.

00:20:25.090 --> 00:20:29.810
We have a page, and we have a
banner, we have drop-down options,

00:20:29.810 --> 00:20:31.860
we have checkboxes.

00:20:31.860 --> 00:20:37.580
And visually presented, when we
are using CSS best practices,

00:20:37.580 --> 00:20:39.200
the content looks beautiful.

00:20:39.200 --> 00:20:46.020
But what happens when the content
itself is not properly ordered

00:20:46.020 --> 00:20:48.920
or is not properly organized?

00:20:48.920 --> 00:20:53.310
The screen reader will not be
able to understand the structure

00:20:53.310 --> 00:20:54.440
of the page.

00:20:54.440 --> 00:20:57.360
So that's why it's really
important for me to share

00:20:57.360 --> 00:21:00.340
with you the Accessibility
Tree concept.

00:21:00.340 --> 00:21:03.890
In this case, you will be
able to understand what would

00:21:03.890 --> 00:21:08.100
be the way your content can be
accessed by using a screen reader.

00:21:08.100 --> 00:21:13.290
For example, on the screen, I have
a screenshot of an horizon beach.

00:21:13.290 --> 00:21:19.150
And as part of the Chrome
options, you can find a small icon

00:21:19.150 --> 00:21:24.370
at the top-right side of the
screenshot that is a small icon,

00:21:25.580 --> 00:21:30.120
like, it’s simulates as a
person, and you can enable that.

00:21:30.120 --> 00:21:35.520
So immediately,
you can convert your code in the way

00:21:35.520 --> 00:21:38.800
that the screen reader
will read your information.

00:21:38.800 --> 00:21:42.850
So you will immediately know
what would be the best way

00:21:42.850 --> 00:21:45.490
that the user can
access our content.

00:21:45.490 --> 00:21:50.310
Now you can just double check
the code, change the components,

00:21:50.310 --> 00:21:54.860
the order of the elements,
add additional attributes or roles

00:21:54.860 --> 00:21:58.070
that can help the screen reader
user to understand the content

00:21:58.070 --> 00:22:01.150
in a logical and meaningful way.

00:22:01.150 --> 00:22:03.350
So that is really,
really important, OK?

00:22:06.110 --> 00:22:10.210
Another point that is really
interesting for me to know,

00:22:10.210 --> 00:22:16.830
because it is one of the most
complicated and most common defects

00:22:16.830 --> 00:22:19.661
when we are navigating
visualizations,

00:22:19.662 --> 00:22:21.330
is the use of keyword.

00:22:21.330 --> 00:22:22.440
What is that?

00:22:22.440 --> 00:22:27.970
We usually get used to navigating
our pages using the mouse

00:22:27.970 --> 00:22:29.850
because it's the best way.

00:22:29.850 --> 00:22:36.590
In the past when I had some
reviews with designers,

00:22:36.590 --> 00:22:39.720
we usually proceed
with a few exercises.

00:22:39.720 --> 00:22:46.800
So how much time do you take to go
to a specific main navigation menu

00:22:46.800 --> 00:22:47.840
using the mouse?

00:22:47.840 --> 00:22:50.480
Three seconds, five seconds.

00:22:50.480 --> 00:22:55.130
What will be the average time
navigating the same navigation menu

00:22:55.130 --> 00:22:58.530
using your keyboard alone?

00:22:58.530 --> 00:23:00.200
Would that will be the same?

00:23:00.200 --> 00:23:01.200
Definitely not, right?

00:23:02.800 --> 00:23:04.530
So you could take two
minutes, three minutes.

00:23:04.530 --> 00:23:05.530
And [Inaudible 00:23:05].

00:23:06.340 --> 00:23:11.580
The main navigation menu
have a lot of options,

00:23:11.580 --> 00:23:15.190
so it will be really difficult
and time consuming for the user

00:23:15.190 --> 00:23:17.370
to navigate the content.

00:23:17.370 --> 00:23:19.380
So that's why it's
really important for you

00:23:19.380 --> 00:23:23.290
to understand that
[Inaudible 00:23:20]

00:23:23.290 --> 00:23:25.540
on the selection of the components.

00:23:25.540 --> 00:23:27.670
And you need to create
custom [Inaudible 00:23:27]

00:23:27.670 --> 00:23:30.020
components; it's also important.

00:23:30.020 --> 00:23:35.830
When you create filters, or when you
create horizontal navigation menus,

00:23:35.830 --> 00:23:39.290
all these things needs to
have a specific strategy

00:23:39.290 --> 00:23:41.390
or keyboard interaction strategy.

00:23:41.390 --> 00:23:46.110
So you can create visual
guidelines to indicate to the user

00:23:46.110 --> 00:23:48.720
what will be the shortcuts,
for example, to access

00:23:48.720 --> 00:23:52.580
to the horizontal toolbar
or the horizontal menu bar?

00:23:52.580 --> 00:23:58.630
So what would be another two
points that you need to consider

00:23:58.630 --> 00:24:01.350
when we are talking about
keyword interaction?

00:24:01.350 --> 00:24:04.160
We already talked about
native components,

00:24:04.161 --> 00:24:09.520
which are usually really good
and beneficial for screen readers.

00:24:09.520 --> 00:24:13.110
But in this case,
it's also necessary to understand

00:24:13.110 --> 00:24:20.720
that every native component from HTML
has their own keyboard interaction.

00:24:20.720 --> 00:24:23.340
It's not the same way you
navigate using a radio group

00:24:23.340 --> 00:24:25.750
or you navigate a checkbox.

00:24:25.750 --> 00:24:29.300
So you can access the
checkbox using the tab key,

00:24:29.300 --> 00:24:33.780
but you need to enable the
checkbox by pressing the space bar.

00:24:33.780 --> 00:24:37.190
In the case of radio groups,
you can access the radio group

00:24:37.190 --> 00:24:39.580
using the tab key,
and you need to navigate

00:24:39.580 --> 00:24:43.260
between the radio groups
using up and down arrows.

00:24:43.260 --> 00:24:48.190
Those are patterns that are also
necessary to keep into consideration

00:24:48.190 --> 00:24:51.080
when you are selecting
those components.

00:24:51.080 --> 00:24:52.350
Why is this important?

00:24:52.350 --> 00:24:56.140
Because it will be meaningful
or not for people that are blind

00:24:56.140 --> 00:25:01.870
or depends on a screen reader, or
also depends on keyboard navigation.

00:25:02.880 --> 00:25:05.445
On the other side,
when we are navigating

00:25:05.446 --> 00:25:07.400
or creating complex components,

00:25:07.400 --> 00:25:12.330
because yes or yes, we need to
customize our visualizations,

00:25:12.330 --> 00:25:17.370
our controls, it will be necessary
to understand that consistency

00:25:17.370 --> 00:25:18.670
is the key.

00:25:18.670 --> 00:25:22.970
So if we are just replicating
the use of one component

00:25:22.970 --> 00:25:27.850
or complex component in another
visualization, we need to understand

00:25:27.850 --> 00:25:31.350
what will be the
purpose of this control.

00:25:31.350 --> 00:25:36.950
So try to create a control with
the same consistent navigation

00:25:36.950 --> 00:25:41.620
that will be replicable
to all other sections.

00:25:41.620 --> 00:25:44.330
Three important points
with the complex components

00:25:44.330 --> 00:25:48.500
when you are creating visualizations,
a structural navigation.

00:25:48.500 --> 00:25:52.170
What will be the specific
structure of your visualization?

00:25:52.170 --> 00:25:55.537
It means the logical,
meaningful navigation

00:25:55.538 --> 00:25:59.700
when the user is navigating
with the tab key, for example.

00:25:59.700 --> 00:26:01.580
Then we have the
spatial navigation.

00:26:02.800 --> 00:26:07.160
What will be the logical way
to access that visualization?

00:26:07.160 --> 00:26:11.930
It will be top, then down,
then up, then down again.

00:26:11.930 --> 00:26:14.910
What will be the specific
interactions that you are looking for

00:26:14.910 --> 00:26:16.710
with this visualization?

00:26:16.710 --> 00:26:18.960
Finally, targeted visualization.

00:26:18.960 --> 00:26:26.960
So how can we create spaces for
the user to be fully concentrated

00:26:27.430 --> 00:26:29.620
in our visualization?

00:26:29.620 --> 00:26:31.530
So [Inaudible 00:26:30]

00:26:31.530 --> 00:26:36.990
we are expecting from our user
in terms of navigation with

00:26:36.990 --> 00:26:39.280
or in regards with
this visualization.

00:26:39.280 --> 00:26:41.240
That’s why it's really important.

00:26:41.240 --> 00:26:46.960
It’s not the same to navigate
through a scatter plot

00:26:46.960 --> 00:26:49.130
and through an Instagram.

00:26:49.130 --> 00:26:50.850
It's not the same, right?

00:26:50.850 --> 00:26:55.260
But if we are using a similar
complex components that I can use

00:26:55.260 --> 00:26:58.030
to filter the information
in a scatter plot,

00:26:58.030 --> 00:27:00.630
but I can use the same
component in the Instagram,

00:27:00.630 --> 00:27:04.260
the consistency will
be the key here, OK?

00:27:04.260 --> 00:27:05.260
Perfect.

00:27:05.850 --> 00:27:09.780
So set of best practices
that can help you.

00:27:09.780 --> 00:27:12.670
ARIA Authoring Practices Guide.

00:27:12.670 --> 00:27:20.590
In this page, you will find the
most-accepted interaction patterns

00:27:20.590 --> 00:27:24.685
for the screen readers,
keyboard navigation patterns

00:27:24.686 --> 00:27:31.040
for keyboard users, for the
HTML5 components from websites.

00:27:31.040 --> 00:27:37.610
So you can find the most important
references [Inaudible 00:27:25],

00:27:37.610 --> 00:27:42.820
which is the organization in charge
to create the way accessibility area

00:27:42.820 --> 00:27:43.820
best practices.

00:27:44.930 --> 00:27:50.850
So in this guide, you will find
multiple best practices you can use

00:27:50.850 --> 00:27:57.360
and incorporate in your code, or you
can replicate in multiple CMS, OK?

00:27:57.360 --> 00:27:58.590
Perfect.

00:27:58.590 --> 00:28:03.780
The next point is that you
need to define a control system

00:28:03.780 --> 00:28:05.500
or an accessibility matrix.

00:28:05.500 --> 00:28:12.580
Do you remember that I talked
about this team that was able

00:28:12.580 --> 00:28:15.530
to create all the colors available?

00:28:15.530 --> 00:28:17.350
So you can use all of
them, whatever you want.

00:28:17.350 --> 00:28:21.060
You can customize with the
colors that you want, OK?

00:28:21.060 --> 00:28:25.730
But sometimes it's really difficult
to determine if a combination

00:28:25.730 --> 00:28:30.930
of a specific set of colors will
create [Inaudible 00:28:28].

00:28:30.930 --> 00:28:35.950
Yes, we can provide this type
of freedom to our customers

00:28:35.950 --> 00:28:40.490
that will be really great,
but it's always our responsibility

00:28:40.490 --> 00:28:45.670
to create best practices also
that we can share to our users

00:28:45.670 --> 00:28:49.440
to create spaces that will
be accessible for them.

00:28:49.440 --> 00:28:50.900
How can we do that?

00:28:50.900 --> 00:28:55.350
So we have our color palette
and we can just match

00:28:55.350 --> 00:29:00.810
what will be the contrast that will
match best with the combinations.

00:29:00.810 --> 00:29:04.960
And you can create a specific
guideline that says, OK,

00:29:04.960 --> 00:29:09.870
so those colors are matching
the minimum requirements

00:29:09.870 --> 00:29:13.780
in terms of colors,
contrast, background,

00:29:13.780 --> 00:29:17.320
foreground regarding the Web
Content Accessibility guidelines,

00:29:17.320 --> 00:29:18.400
for example.

00:29:18.400 --> 00:29:22.880
So you can create a specific scenario
that you can share with them,

00:29:22.880 --> 00:29:25.780
and they can manipulate
information in a way

00:29:25.780 --> 00:29:29.649
that can create
customized environments

00:29:29.650 --> 00:29:32.550
that are also accessible, OK?

00:29:32.550 --> 00:29:35.950
Another important point
that I would like to mention

00:29:35.950 --> 00:29:39.130
is the pattern library.

00:29:39.130 --> 00:29:44.710
So what happens if I tell you
that color blindness is one

00:29:44.710 --> 00:29:49.590
of the most common disability
that we can find right now

00:29:49.590 --> 00:29:52.140
when we are talking
about visualizations?

00:29:52.140 --> 00:29:55.060
And I'm telling you this
because I was working

00:29:55.060 --> 00:30:02.170
with a specific area full of men,
and most of them, incredibly,

00:30:02.170 --> 00:30:05.230
had color blindness condition,
and they didn't know

00:30:05.230 --> 00:30:10.100
until they started working with
a specific product of the system.

00:30:11.990 --> 00:30:15.030
So what will be the
recommendations?

00:30:15.030 --> 00:30:19.070
Always try to create
a pattern library.

00:30:19.070 --> 00:30:20.560
What is the meaning of that?

00:30:20.560 --> 00:30:27.790
Try to create a specific
selection of lines, dots, icons,

00:30:29.770 --> 00:30:33.710
backgrounds, templates,
everything that can help you

00:30:33.710 --> 00:30:39.200
to create the content in a way that
can be accessible for other users,

00:30:39.200 --> 00:30:40.200
OK?

00:30:40.200 --> 00:30:47.180
I have for an example for that,
and this is a really good scenario.

00:30:47.180 --> 00:30:52.570
So we have on the screen a pie
chart that is using a specific set

00:30:52.570 --> 00:30:53.810
of colors.

00:30:53.810 --> 00:30:58.470
This is an accessible way
to present to the customer.

00:30:58.470 --> 00:31:05.250
So if you can click on the enable
color patterns, you can find

00:31:05.250 --> 00:31:11.030
what will be the specific
pattern or specific sections

00:31:11.030 --> 00:31:14.090
that were designed for
each of the colors.

00:31:14.090 --> 00:31:21.900
For example, you can definitely
identify that each color is

00:31:21.900 --> 00:31:26.260
with a specific pattern.

00:31:29.810 --> 00:31:33.500
So you can see how important it is.

00:31:33.500 --> 00:31:38.540
For people that are not able to
just distinguish multiple colors,

00:31:38.540 --> 00:31:44.310
you can enable small sections like
this and enable a background pattern

00:31:44.310 --> 00:31:48.040
so you can better
identify your content.

00:31:50.570 --> 00:31:56.230
Another point that is
really interesting here is,

00:31:56.230 --> 00:32:02.060
I had multiple conversations
with the technical writers.

00:32:02.060 --> 00:32:10.060
I'm probably using technical
writers while we are talking

00:32:12.910 --> 00:32:15.340
about technical writers.

00:32:15.340 --> 00:32:19.360
The language that we are using
to create our components,

00:32:19.360 --> 00:32:21.490
it's also important.

00:32:21.490 --> 00:32:26.330
We talk about learning disabilities,
cognitive disabilities,

00:32:26.330 --> 00:32:29.920
mental health,
and any other type of disability

00:32:29.920 --> 00:32:35.980
that can directly impact the
opportunity to make decisions.

00:32:35.980 --> 00:32:43.480
So the content needs to be simple
as much as in the technical areas

00:32:43.480 --> 00:32:44.780
that we are, right?

00:32:44.780 --> 00:32:49.670
Not in all spaces we can
just change the word probably

00:32:49.670 --> 00:32:51.990
because the profile or
the type of audience

00:32:51.990 --> 00:32:55.130
that will access that information
will not be familiar with that.

00:32:55.130 --> 00:32:58.860
So that is really important
for us to understand that.

00:33:00.680 --> 00:33:07.440
My recommendation is that, for the
designers and developers, always try

00:33:07.440 --> 00:33:11.220
to have a technical writer,
or a technical person

00:33:11.220 --> 00:33:15.540
that can help you to use the
specific words that will be easy

00:33:15.540 --> 00:33:18.750
to understand when you are
creating customized components

00:33:18.750 --> 00:33:22.700
on your visualizations, because
it will be the best way for you

00:33:22.700 --> 00:33:25.164
to create content that
will be accessible,

