00:37:38.670 --> 00:37:42.218
Usually, when we think that
accessibility is something

00:37:42.219 --> 00:37:48.900
that is ugly or it would be difficult
to implement, that is not true, OK?

00:37:48.900 --> 00:37:51.240
It could take discussions.

00:37:51.240 --> 00:37:53.380
It could take conversations.

00:37:53.380 --> 00:37:55.010
It could take adiations.

00:37:55.010 --> 00:37:59.580
But it’s always possible to
create accessible content.

00:38:01.170 --> 00:38:04.540
Sometimes we say we
need to create something

00:38:04.540 --> 00:38:08.780
that will be completely
accessible, and it is not possible

00:38:08.780 --> 00:38:12.660
to create something 100%.

00:38:12.660 --> 00:38:15.723
So it’s necessary
for us to understand

00:38:15.724 --> 00:38:18.000
that we can create something

00:38:18.000 --> 00:38:23.850
that will be equivalent,
or we can create multiple contexts

00:38:23.850 --> 00:38:28.580
that can help us to create accessible
environments in a specific page

00:38:28.580 --> 00:38:31.750
that is using multiple
components that are complex.

00:38:31.750 --> 00:38:39.180
Of course, always try to create and
identify your components in a way

00:38:39.180 --> 00:38:41.820
that will be accessible
as much as possible.

00:38:41.820 --> 00:38:48.190
For example, if you are using a
theme that is accessible already,

00:38:48.190 --> 00:38:52.230
but there are some specific
sections that are not possible

00:38:52.230 --> 00:38:56.910
to customize,
always prepare yourself, your team.

00:38:56.910 --> 00:39:04.910
Create a specific accessibility
exception document

00:39:07.800 --> 00:39:11.490
so you can add all the restrictions
that you have with the system.

00:39:11.490 --> 00:39:13.980
Because it's necessary
for you to understand

00:39:13.980 --> 00:39:19.640
that sometimes we are working with
sites that are already created,

00:39:19.640 --> 00:39:23.480
and they didn't think about
accessibility at the beginning,

00:39:23.480 --> 00:39:27.040
and now it’ll be a little bit
difficult to implement accessibility.

00:39:27.040 --> 00:39:30.310
So it will be necessary
for you to identify

00:39:30.310 --> 00:39:34.290
what will be the best strategy
to create a content for them

00:39:34.290 --> 00:39:35.320
and make it accessible.

00:39:37.000 --> 00:39:42.450
Of course, try to create a
set of [Inaudible 00:39:41]

00:39:42.450 --> 00:39:48.660
to understand what accessibility
go to in terms of their industry

00:39:48.660 --> 00:39:52.160
and the type of audience that
will be [Inaudible 00:39:49].

00:39:52.160 --> 00:39:56.210
Finally, one of the things that
I would like to mention is that,

00:39:56.210 --> 00:40:00.240
always know the purpose
of the visualization.

00:40:00.240 --> 00:40:04.120
Don't just create visualization
because, yes, right?

00:40:04.120 --> 00:40:08.070
Always create visualizations
with a meaning.

00:40:08.070 --> 00:40:12.160
Always try to humanize the
visualization as much as possible.

00:40:12.160 --> 00:40:15.123
Consider the different disabilities

00:40:15.124 --> 00:40:18.510
that we talked about
at the beginning.

00:40:18.510 --> 00:40:23.050
Always consider disabilities
from the first planning session,

00:40:23.050 --> 00:40:27.130
not during the coding session
or during the testing session

00:40:27.130 --> 00:40:29.590
or even after the first launch.

00:40:29.590 --> 00:40:30.750
No, no, no, no.

00:40:30.750 --> 00:40:34.630
It's necessary for you to understand
that disability needs to be part

00:40:34.630 --> 00:40:36.680
of the conversation always.

00:40:36.680 --> 00:40:40.090
